     第６章　受動態
============================================================ -->

<div class="chapter" id="ch6">
<div class="chapter-header">
  <div class="ch-num">CHAPTER 06</div>
  <h2>受動態</h2>
  <p>受動態は「〜される」という意味で、目的語を主語に持ち上げるときに使う。基本形から助動詞を含む形、SVOO・SVOCの受動態、群動詞の受動態まで体系的に整理する。</p>
</div>

<div class="section" id="s6-1">
<h3>6.1 基本の受動態</h3>

<div class="formula-box theorem">
<strong>受動態の基本形：be動詞 + 過去分詞（+ by 〜）</strong>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
  <tr><th>時制</th><th>能動態</th><th>受動態</th></tr>
  <tr><td>現在</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">They clean the room.</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">The room <strong>is cleaned</strong>.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>過去</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">They cleaned the room.</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">The room <strong>was cleaned</strong>.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>現在完了</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">They have cleaned the room.</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">The room <strong>has been cleaned</strong>.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>進行形</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">They are cleaning the room.</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">The room <strong>is being cleaned</strong>.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td>助動詞あり</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">They will clean the room.</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">The room <strong>will be cleaned</strong>.</span></td></tr>
</table></div>
</div>

<div class="tip-box">
<strong>by 以外の前置詞を使う受動態慣用表現</strong><br>
<span class="eng">be known <strong>to</strong></span>（〜に知られている）/ <span class="eng">be known <strong>for</strong></span>（〜で知られている）<br>
<span class="eng">be surprised <strong>at</strong></span>（〜に驚く）/ <span class="eng">be satisfied <strong>with</strong></span>（〜に満足している）<br>
<span class="eng">be interested <strong>in</strong></span>（〜に興味がある）/ <span class="eng">be made <strong>of</strong></span>（〜でできている、材料が見える）<br>
<span class="eng">be made <strong>from</strong></span>（〜でできている、材料が変化）/ <span class="eng">be covered <strong>with</strong></span>（〜で覆われている）
</div>
</div><!-- /s6-1 -->

<div class="section" id="s6-2">
<h3>6.2 SVOO・SVOCの受動態</h3>

<div class="formula-box pattern">
<strong>SVOO → 受動態（2通り）</strong><br>
<span class="eng">They gave <strong>her</strong> a present.</span>（間接目的語 her ／直接目的語 a present）<br>
→ <span class="eng"><strong>She</strong> was given a present.</span>（間接目的語が主語）<br>
→ <span class="eng"><strong>A present</strong> was given to her.</span>（直接目的語が主語、前置詞が必要）
</div>

<div class="formula-box pattern">
<strong>SVOC → 受動態</strong><br>
補語（C）の形が動詞の種類によって異なる。
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
  <tr><th>能動態</th><th>受動態</th></tr>
  <tr><td class="left"><span class="eng">They <strong>made</strong> him clean the room.</span>（make + 原形）</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">He was made <strong>to clean</strong> the room.</span>（受動態では to が復活）</td></tr>
  <tr><td class="left"><span class="eng">I <strong>saw</strong> her crossing the street.</span>（知覚動詞 + -ing）</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">She was seen <strong>crossing</strong> the street.</span>（-ingはそのまま）</td></tr>
  <tr><td class="left"><span class="eng">They <strong>called</strong> him a genius.</span>（call + 名詞）</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">He was called a genius.</span></td></tr>
</table></div>
</div>
</div><!-- /s6-2 -->

<div class="section" id="s6-3">
<h3>6.3 群動詞・注意すべき受動態</h3>

<div class="formula-box">
<strong>群動詞（phrasal verb）の受動態</strong><br>
群動詞は「動詞＋前置詞/副詞」の組み合わせで1つの動詞として機能する。受動態にするときも<strong>群動詞全体をひとまとめに扱う</strong>。<br><br>
<span class="eng">They <strong>laughed at</strong> him.</span> → <span class="eng">He was <strong>laughed at</strong>.</span><br>
<span class="eng">She <strong>took care of</strong> the baby.</span> → <span class="eng">The baby was <strong>taken care of</strong>.</span><br>
<span class="eng">People <strong>look up to</strong> him.</span> → <span class="eng">He is <strong>looked up to</strong>.</span>
</div>

<div class="exercise-block">
<strong>練習 6.1</strong>　次の能動態を受動態に書き換えよ。<br>
(1) The teacher told us an interesting story.<br>
(2) They made the children wait outside.<br>
(3) People speak highly of her work.
<div class="answer-block">
(1) <span class="eng">We were told an interesting story by the teacher.</span><br>
　　（or <span class="eng">An interesting story was told to us by the teacher.</span>）<br>
(2) <span class="eng">The children were made to wait outside.</span>（make → 受動態で to が復活）<br>
(3) <span class="eng">Her work is spoken highly of.</span>（群動詞 speak highly of をひとまとまりに）
</div>
</div>
</div><!-- /s6-3 -->
</div><!-- /ch6 -->

