     第７章　比較表現
============================================================ -->

<div class="chapter" id="ch7">
<div class="chapter-header">
  <div class="ch-num">CHAPTER 07</div>
  <h2>比較表現</h2>
  <p>英語の比較構文は原級・比較級・最上級の3段階が基本。さらに「倍数表現」「no more than系」「the＋比較級…the＋比較級」など入試頻出の慣用的表現も体系的に整理する。</p>
</div>

<div class="section" id="s7-1">
<h3>7.1 原級比較・as...as 構文</h3>

<div class="formula-box theorem">
<strong>as + 原級 + as の主要パターン</strong>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
  <tr><th>形</th><th>意味</th><th>例</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">as + adj./adv. + as</span></td><td>〜と同じくらい…だ</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">She is as tall as him.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">not as[so] + adj. + as</span></td><td>〜ほど…でない</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">He is not as clever as she is.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">as + adj. + as possible</span></td><td>できる限り…</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">Come as soon as possible.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">as + adj. + as + S + can</span></td><td>〃（as…as S can）</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">Run as fast as you can.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">twice[three times] as + adj. + as</span></td><td>〜の2倍[3倍]…だ</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">This bag is twice as heavy as that one.</span></td></tr>
</table></div>
</div>
</div><!-- /s7-1 -->

<div class="section" id="s7-2">
<h3>7.2 比較級・最上級</h3>

<div class="formula-box">
<strong>比較級・最上級の作り方</strong>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
  <tr><th>種類</th><th>比較級</th><th>最上級</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1音節・規則変化</td><td>-er</td><td>-est</td></tr>
  <tr><td>-e で終わる語</td><td>-r</td><td>-st</td></tr>
  <tr><td>「短母音＋子音」終わり</td><td>子音字重ねて -er</td><td>子音字重ねて -est</td></tr>
  <tr><td>「子音字＋y」終わり</td><td>y→i＋er</td><td>y→i＋est</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2音節以上</td><td>more +原級</td><td>most +原級</td></tr>
</table></div>
</div>

<div class="formula-box pattern">
<strong>比較級の重要構文</strong>
<ul class="bullet">
<li><strong>比較級 + than any other + 単数名詞：</strong><span class="eng">Tokyo is larger than any other city in Japan.</span></li>
<li><strong>No (other) + 単数名詞 + is as + 原級 + as：</strong><span class="eng">No other city in Japan is as large as Tokyo.</span></li>
<li><strong>the + 比較級 …, the + 比較級 〜：</strong><span class="eng">The harder you try, the better you get.</span>（努力すればするほど、上達する）</li>
<li><strong>比較級 + and + 比較級：</strong><span class="eng">It's getting colder and colder.</span>（どんどん寒くなっている）</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div><!-- /s7-2 -->

<div class="section" id="s7-3">
<h3>7.3 倍数・差の表現</h3>

<div class="formula-box">
<strong>倍数・差の表現</strong>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
  <tr><th>表現</th><th>意味</th><th>例</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">twice as … as</span></td><td>2倍…</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">This room is twice as large as mine.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">half as … as</span></td><td>半分しか…ない</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">He earns half as much as I do.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">much / far + 比較級</span></td><td>ずっと〜</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">She is far more capable than him.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">a little / slightly + 比較級</span></td><td>少し〜</td><td class="left"><span class="eng">The new model is slightly heavier.</span></td></tr>
</table></div>
</div>
</div><!-- /s7-3 -->

<div class="section" id="s7-4">
<h3>7.4 no more than など重要比較表現</h3>

<div class="formula-box important">
<strong>紛らわしい比較表現4組</strong>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
  <tr><th>表現</th><th>意味</th><th>同義</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng"><strong>no more than</strong> 5</span></td><td>わずか5しかない</td><td>only 5</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng"><strong>not more than</strong> 5</span></td><td>5以下</td><td>at most 5</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng"><strong>no less than</strong> 5</span></td><td>5もある（多さを強調）</td><td>as many/much as 5</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng"><strong>not less than</strong> 5</span></td><td>少なくとも5</td><td>at least 5</td></tr>
</table></div>
<strong>no more A than B（クジラ構文）：</strong>AではないのはBではないのと同様だ（どちらも否定）<br>
<span class="eng">A whale is no more a fish than a horse is.</span>（クジラが魚でないのは馬が魚でないのと同じだ）
</div>

<div class="exercise-block">
<strong>練習 7.1</strong>　和訳せよ。<br>
(1) The more you read, the more you know.<br>
(2) She earned no less than a million dollars last year.<br>
(3) He is no more a poet than I am.
<div class="answer-block">
(1)「読めば読むほど、知識が増える。」（the＋比較級…the＋比較級）<br>
(2)「彼女は昨年100万ドルも稼いだ。」（no less than ＝ 多さを強調）<br>
(3)「彼が詩人でないのは、私が詩人でないのと同じだ。」（no more A than B ＝ どちらも〜でない）
</div>
</div>
</div><!-- /s7-4 -->
</div><!-- /ch7 -->

<!-- ============================================================
     第８章　特殊構文
============================================================ -->

<div class="chapter" id="ch8">
<div class="chapter-header">
  <div class="ch-num">CHAPTER 08</div>
  <h2>特殊構文</h2>
  <p>強調・倒置・省略・否定表現など、入試で問われる頻度の高い特殊な構文を整理する。形と意味の対応を正確に覚えることが重要。</p>
</div>

<div class="section" id="s8-1">
<h3>8.1 強調構文</h3>

<div class="formula-box theorem">
<strong>It is [was] ... that 〜 の強調構文</strong><br>
強調したい要素（主語・目的語・副詞（句/節））を <em>It is ... that</em> の <em>...</em> の部分に持ち込む。強調される要素が人の場合、<em>that</em> の代わりに <em>who</em> が使えることがある。<br><br>
<span class="eng">Tom broke the window yesterday in the park.</span>（基本文）<br>
→ <span class="eng">It was <strong>Tom</strong> that[who] broke the window.</span>（Tomを強調）<br>
→ <span class="eng">It was <strong>the window</strong> that Tom broke.</span>（窓を強調）<br>
→ <span class="eng">It was <strong>yesterday</strong> that Tom broke the window.</span>（昨日を強調）
</div>

<div class="important-box">
<strong>強調構文 vs 形式主語構文の見分け方</strong><br>
<em>It is ... that</em> の <em>that</em> 以下を取り除いても文が成立する → <strong>強調構文</strong><br>
<em>that</em> 以下を取り除くと文が成立しない → <strong>形式主語構文</strong><br><br>
<span class="eng">It is <strong>strange</strong> that he is absent.</span>（形式主語：that節がないと成立しない）<br>
<span class="eng">It was <strong>here</strong> that she found her wallet.</span>（強調：「She found her wallet.」として成立）
</div>
</div><!-- /s8-1 -->

<div class="section" id="s8-2">
<h3>8.2 倒置</h3>

<div class="formula-box theorem">
<strong>否定語・否定的意味の副詞（句/節）の倒置</strong><br>
否定の副詞表現が文頭に来ると、主語と（助）動詞が倒置する。
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
  <tr><th>副詞表現</th><th>例文</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">Never</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng"><strong>Never</strong> have I seen such a beautiful sunset.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">Not until …</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng"><strong>Not until midnight</strong> did he come home.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">Hardly / Scarcely … when[before]</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng"><strong>Hardly had</strong> she entered when the phone rang.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">Not only … but also</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng"><strong>Not only</strong> did he lie, but he also denied it.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">Only then / Only when …</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng"><strong>Only then</strong> did I realize my mistake.</span></td></tr>
</table></div>
</div>

<div class="formula-box pattern">
<strong>場所・方向の副詞句の倒置（主語が代名詞でない場合）</strong><br>
<span class="eng">Here <strong>comes the bus</strong>.</span>（バスが来た）<br>
<span class="eng">There <strong>goes our chance</strong>.</span>（チャンスが逃げた）<br>
<span class="note">主語が代名詞の場合は倒置しない：<span class="eng">Here <strong>it comes</strong>.</span>（○）　<span class="red">✗</span> <span class="eng">Here comes it.</span></span>
</div>
</div><!-- /s8-2 -->

<div class="section" id="s8-3">
<h3>8.3 省略</h3>

<div class="formula-box">
<strong>接続詞節内の「主語＋be動詞」省略</strong><br>
接続詞（when / while / if / though / unless / as など）の後ろで、主語が主節と同じ場合、「主語 + be動詞」を省略できる。<br><br>
<span class="eng">While (he was) walking, he listened to music.</span><br>
<span class="eng">If (it is) possible, please come early.</span><br>
<span class="eng">Though (she was) tired, she continued working.</span>
</div>

<div class="formula-box pattern">
<strong>代動詞 do / does / did による省略</strong><br>
前述の述語動詞（句）を繰り返す代わりに do（does/did）を使う。<br>
<span class="eng">She speaks English better than he <strong>does</strong>.</span>（does ＝ speaks English）<br>
<span class="eng">I finished my homework. So <strong>did</strong> Tom.</span>（Tom も終わらせた）<br>
<span class="eng">I didn't expect that. Neither <strong>did</strong> she.</span>（彼女も予期しなかった）
</div>
</div><!-- /s8-3 -->

<div class="section" id="s8-4">
<h3>8.4 否定表現</h3>

<div class="formula-box theorem">
<strong>部分否定 vs 全体否定</strong>
<div class="table-wrap"><table>
  <tr><th>区分</th><th>表現</th><th>例文・意味</th></tr>
  <tr><td rowspan="3"><strong>部分否定</strong><br>（すべてが〜ではない）</td><td><span class="eng">not always</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">Rich people are not always happy.</span>（金持ちが必ずしも幸せとは限らない）</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">not necessarily</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">This is not necessarily true.</span>（必ずしも正しいとは限らない）</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">not both / not all / not every</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">Not all students passed.</span>（すべての学生が合格したわけではない）</td></tr>
  <tr><td rowspan="2"><strong>全体否定</strong><br>（まったく〜ない）</td><td><span class="eng">none / no one / nobody</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">None of them knew the answer.</span></td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="eng">neither / nor</span></td><td class="left"><span class="eng">Neither of them was correct.</span></td></tr>
</table></div>
</div>

<div class="formula-box pattern">
<strong>二重否定・準否定語</strong><br>
<strong>二重否定（強い肯定）：</strong><span class="eng">There is no rule without exceptions.</span>（例外のない規則はない ＝ 必ず例外はある）<br><br>
<strong>準否定語（ほとんど否定）：</strong><br>
<span class="eng">hardly / scarcely（ほとんど〜ない）：</span><span class="eng">I could hardly hear him.</span><br>
<span class="eng">rarely / seldom（めったに〜ない）：</span><span class="eng">She seldom goes out.</span><br>
<span class="eng">little / few（ほとんど〜ない）：</span><span class="eng">He had little interest in sports.</span>
</div>

<div class="exam-card">
<div class="exam-hd"><span>入試頻出問題</span><span class="etag tag-spc">特殊構文</span></div>
<div class="exam-body">
次の文の意味を日本語で述べ、倒置・強調・否定のいずれかを特定せよ。<br>
(1) <span class="eng">It was not until she left that I realized how much I loved her.</span><br>
(2) <span class="eng">Not a word did he say throughout the meeting.</span><br>
(3) <span class="eng">I don't always agree with him.</span>
<div class="answer-block">
(1) 「彼女が去って初めて、私は彼女をどれほど愛していたかに気づいた。」―― <strong>強調構文</strong>（not until〜を強調）<br>
(2) 「彼は会議中ひと言も言わなかった。」―― <strong>否定語（Not a word）による倒置</strong><br>
(3) 「私は必ずしも彼に同意するわけではない。」―― <strong>部分否定</strong>（not always）
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="exercise-block">
<strong>練習 8.1</strong>　強調構文を使って書き換えよ。<br>
(1) She lost her key in the garden last Sunday.（"in the garden"を強調）<br>
(2) Ken told me the truth.（"Ken"を強調）
<div class="answer-block">
(1) <span class="eng">It was in the garden that she lost her key last Sunday.</span><br>
(2) <span class="eng">It was Ken who[that] told me the truth.</span>
</div>
</div>
</div><!-- /s8-4 -->
</div><!-- /ch8 -->

